<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>PROPELLER SHAFT - VIBRATION - PROPELLER SHAFT PHASING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="1">
        <title>PROPELLER SHAFT PHASING</title>
        <para>Propeller shaft phasing is the alignment of the yokes or flanges with each other (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0600136">Figure 36</hotlnk>). A correctly phased propeller shaft is one in which all of the
            yoke bores or flange ears are in alignment with each other.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0600136" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0600136" filename="../figg06/G0600136.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="152px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 36. Propeller Shaft Phasing</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>Propeller shaft phasing can be altered by incorrect reassembly of the slip joint. Improper propeller shaft
            phasing can produce excessive vibration.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
